SIMPLE: optometry
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Optometry
<hw>Op*tom"e*try</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<fld>(Med.)</fld> <def>Measurement of the range of vision, esp. by means
of the optometer.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>As defined (with minor variations) in the statutes
of various States of the United States:</def> <sd>(a)</sd>
<def>⟦ldquo⟧The employment of subjective and objective mechanical means
to determine the accomodative and refractive states of the eye and the
scope of its function in general.⟦rdquo⟧</def> <sd>(b)</sd>
<def>⟦ldquo⟧The employment of any means, other than the use of drugs,
for the measurement of the powers of vision and adaptation of lenses for
the aid thereof.⟦rdquo⟧</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Opulence</ent>⟦br⟧
